function trimmedMean(arr) {
    const n = arr.length;
    const remove = Math.floor(n * 0.05);
    arr.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let sum = 0.0;
    for (let i = remove; i < n - remove; i++) {
        sum += arr[i];
    }
    return sum / (n - 2 * remove);
}
```


    1. Calculate the number of elements to remove from each side which is equal to 5% of the array length.
2. Sort the input array in ascending order.
3. Calculate the sum of the remaining elements after removing the smallest 5% and largest 5% of the sorted array.
4. Return the mean for the remaining elements by dividing the sum by `(n - 2 * remove)`.

